The Public Servants Association is in intense negotiations with government this Sunday. Government doesn't look to be moving from its zero percent wage increase. The PSA is demanding, among other things, a 7-percent rise. #eNCA​ Courtesy #DStv403 PRETORIA - Public sector unions and government representatives will resume wage talks today. Unions are demanding a seven-percent increase, while government wants to keep wages at current levels. READ: PSA to protest over wage hikes The Public Servants Association says it hopes the employer will negotiate in good faith.